To export your height-map:Punch F10 to bring up your Render Scene DialogPunch the Render Elements tab in the Render Scene DialogIn the Render Elements Roll-out, click "Add..."Select "Z-Depth" and click "OK"In the Render Scene Dialog (with your Render Elements tab open) scroll all the way down and find the "Z Depth Element Parameters"For your Z-min height, punch in "0 m"For your Z-max height, punch in "128m"In your photo, this will mean that a height of 0m will be pure black, and a height of 128m will be pure whieClick the Common tab (in your Render Scene Dialog)Change your Height and Width to 1024x1024Make sure that the "Displacement" checkbox is Filled.